<Link id="l00119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="119"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="120"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &quot;&lt;func name&gt;&quot;, &#123; &lt;leads&gt; &#125;, &#123; &lt;param rules&gt; &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="121"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// where:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="122"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  &lt;leads&gt; - list of integers that are one-based indexes of formal argument</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="123"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    used to mangle a function name. Other argument types are derived from types</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="124"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    of these &#39;leads&#39;. The order of integers in this list correspond to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="125"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    order in which these arguments are mangled in the EDG mangling scheme. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="126"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    same order should be preserved for arguments in the AMDGPULibFunc structure</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    when it is used for mangling. For example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    &#123; &quot;vstorea&#95;half&quot;, &#123;3,1&#125;, &#123;E&#95;ANY,EX&#95;SIZET,E&#95;ANY&#125;&#125;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    will be mangled in EDG scheme as  vstorea&#95;half&#95;&lt;3dparam&gt;&#95;&lt;1stparam&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="130"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    When mangling from code use:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="131"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    AMDGPULibFunc insc;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    insc.param&#91;0&#93; = ... // describe 3rd parameter</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    insc.param&#91;1&#93; = ... // describe 1rd parameter</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &lt;param rules&gt; - list of rules used to derive all of the function formal</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    argument types. EX&#95; prefixed are simple types, other derived from the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    latest &#39;lead&#39; argument type in the order of encoding from first to last.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    E&#95;ANY - use prev lead type, E&#95;CONSTPTR&#95;ANY - make const pointer out of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    prev lead type, etc. see ParamIterator::getNextParam() for details.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="140"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">nullptr</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">namespace </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Itanium mangling ABI says:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &quot;5.1.8. Compression</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ... Each non-terminal in the grammar for which &lt;substitution&gt; appears on the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// right-hand side is both a source of future substitutions and a candidate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for being substituted. There are two exceptions that appear to be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// substitution candidates from the grammar, but are explicitly excluded:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 &lt;builtin-type&gt; other than vendor extended types ...&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For the purpose of functions the following productions make sense for the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// substitution:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  &lt;type&gt; ::= &lt;builtin-type&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    ::= &lt;class-enum-type&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    ::= &lt;array-type&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    ::=&lt;CV-qualifiers&gt; &lt;type&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00783" /><CodeLine lineNumber="783"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    ::= P &lt;type&gt;                # pointer-to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    ::= &lt;substitution&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note that while types like images, samplers and events are by the ABI encoded</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00787" /><CodeLine lineNumber="787"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// using &lt;class-enum-type&gt; production rule they&#39;re not used for substitution</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Logically, the substitutable components of a mangled name are considered</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// left-to-right, components before the composite structure of which they</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are a part. If a component has been encountered before, it is substituted</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// as described below. This decision is independent of whether its components</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// have been substituted, so an implementation may optimize by considering</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// large structures for substitution before their components. If a component</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// has not been encountered before, its mangling is identified, and it is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// added to a dictionary of substitution candidates. No entity is added to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the dictionary twice.</span></CodeLine>
